node.title: Mystery Adelaide COVID-19 case turns out to be a false positive as SA records four new infections
node.alt: Houses and apartments on a windy road next to the beach
node.description: South Australia records four new COVID-19 cases, while the source of two mystery infections is confirmed.
node.content: ["South Australia has recorded four new COVID-19 cases, while the source of two mystery infections has been confirmed.", "SA Health said today's new cases were two women and two men.", "Two of the infections were acquired interstate, while one was acquired overseas and one locally.", "One of the cases was linked to the Norwood cluster, which now had 25 cases, accounting for more than half of all positive cases since South Australia opened its borders to NSW, Victoria and the ACT on November 23.", "A positive COVID-19 test recorded for a woman who flew from Adelaide to the Northern Territory after spending time in Port Noarlunga, in Adelaide's southern suburbs, last week had been identified as a false positive.", "That case prompted the NT government to tighten border restrictions with SA.", "A separate mystery case identified yesterday has now been classified as interstate acquired.", "South Australia has recorded 971 COVID-19 cases since the start of the coronavirus pandemic, including 49 since the state's eastern border\u00a0reopened.", "More to come."]
